## Cohesion Audit: David-Beckham.md

### Central Thesis
The world sees an effortless golden boy handed everything; understanding Type 3 reveals Beckham built every inch of it himself and cannot stop building, because he learned as a boy that love is earned by delivering, and once, for three years, an entire nation showed him how fast that love turns to hate.

### Thread Map
| # | Section | What it argues | Link to the one before |
|---|---------|----------------|------------------------|
| — | Intro (candles / night watchman) | The 2am ritual disproves the "handed everything" myth; the perfection was assembled from inside | Sets the thesis |
| 1 | *What is his personality type?* | Defines the Type 3 engine; Ferguson + Neville prove built-not-gifted; reserve = sp-3 counter-type; **teases the fridge** | Turns the intro's ritual into a diagnosis |
| 2 | *The father who took him out for hours* | Origin of the engine: love-as-transaction, "get on with it"; 2am rendered from inside; **pays off the fridge** | Answers "how was a Three made?" |
| 3 | *Why an entire nation turned on him* | The wound that supercharges the engine: loved-for-one-thing = destroyable-for-one-thing; he answers by delivering (timeline); billboard-as-insurance | The private arena where "the verdict is always his" flips to the public arena where it wasn't |
| 4 | *How he built a brand out of a haircut* | The insurance in action: image as second career, staged reveals, flying boot turned into a photo, Ronaldo inherits the blueprint | "He built a life with more than one thing in it" → here's how |
| 5 | *Why the marriage survived its worst year* | The marriage was the brand's founding act; rebuilt under threat; Brooklyn estrangement = the one arena the self-builder can't deliver his way out of | "Beckham had already drawn the blueprint" → the marriage was the first draft of it |
| — | Rabbit Hole (quarantined) | Wings/subtype/arrows/counterargs | Skippable buffer |
| 6 | *Why he took the Qatar money* | The pattern at its most morally costly; honest critic pressure; Messi delivered; knighthood = effigy come full circle | Returns to the delivery pattern at full throttle |
| 7 | *The straight lines still have to hold* | Loved-hated-loved; more rooms than any crowd can burn; the son walks out; back to 2am; the crowd he can't win is himself | "Answered every wound by building bigger" → and the one place building fails |

The outline reads coherently top-to-bottom. That is itself the headline finding: **there is no thread break anywhere in this piece.**

### Scores
| Check | Score | Issues |
|-------|-------|--------|
| Through-Line Clarity | 10/10 | 0 |
| Promise-Delivery Match | 10/10 | 0 |
| Reader Mental Model | 9/10 | 1 |
| Section Transitions | 8/10 | 1 |
| Internal Paragraph Flow | 9/10 | 0 |

**Overall Cohesion Score: 9/10**

### Transition detail
- **Intro → myth → "candles give it away"**: Strong. The night-watchman ritual is set directly against the "gods handed him the ticket" myth, then the candles are named as the evidence.
- **Type-3 tease "the clue lives in the fridge, we will get there" → father section**: Strong. A deliberate suspense hook, held across the childhood narrative and paid off by Victoria's fridge quote at that section's close. Nothing orphaned.
- **Father → crisis**: Strong-implicit. Section ends "the one arena where the verdict is always his"; the crisis is the arena where the verdict was taken from him entirely. The inner-thought paragraph pre-loads the contrast ("Out there, the crowd decides... In here, tonight, he decides"), so the H2 carries the bridge without a seam sentence.
- **Crisis → brand**: Adequate-to-strong. "He built a life with more than one thing in it... insurance" hands off to the image as a "second career running alongside the first." One real tonal shift (grave → wry haircut cold-open), but it's a deliberate stylistic beat, not a logic gap.
- **Brand → marriage**: Strong. "Beckham had already drawn the blueprint" → "It was the founding act of the brand." The keyword *brand* carries and recontextualizes.
- **Marriage → Qatar** (the one soft seam): Adequate. The marriage section escalates to the thesis's *limit* (the arena consent won't let him build), then Qatar rewinds to 2022 and returns to triumph. The Rabbit Hole physically buffers the two, and the closing re-gathers the Brooklyn thread, so it's suspended, not dropped. Still the weakest join in the piece.
- **Qatar → close**: Strong. Knighthood just landed; "answered every wound by building bigger" flows straight into the summation and the return to the 2am ritual.

### Verdict
This is already a cohesive piece (9/10). Every section earns its place, the promise from title/description/intro is fully delivered, and the one forward-reference (the fridge) is paid off cleanly. Per the cohesion-check protocol, at 8+ I stop and check with you rather than manufacturing bridges, because the two candidate spots are exactly where a forced transition would read as mechanical and *lower* the score.

The only judgment call worth your eye:

**The marriage → Qatar seam.** After the Brooklyn estrangement (the thesis's hardest test, set in 2026), the Qatar section steps back to 2022 for another delivery-triumph lap. My recommendation is **leave it as-is**: the Rabbit Hole buffers the reader reset, and the closing deliberately re-picks-up Brooklyn ("a grown son can walk out of the frame and refuse to be arranged"). Forcing a bridge from "the arena he can't win" straight into "here's another arena he won" would flatten the honest downbeat you built. The suspension is working for you.

Do you want me to:
1. **Leave it untouched** (my recommendation — it's ship-ready on cohesion), or
2. Attempt a one-sentence bridge at the top of the Qatar section to smooth that single seam (I'd draft it in Beckham's voice, no mechanical "moving on to" filler), or
3. Anything else you noticed reading it?

I made no edits.
