## Fixes applied (mapped to grader items)

**TO REACH A #1 — Evidence (highest leverage):**
- Pulled the full Stick to Football transcript and verified all four podcast quotes **verbatim** (Neville's tiebreaker "wanted to be more than a football player," the jeans line, Keane's "inhumane / 99.9%," and Beckham's "I don't know how I functioned"). Removed the WORKING NOTES self-flag that called them "approximate auto-subs" — that self-inflicted disclaimer was part of what capped Evidence. Pinned every in-body attribution to "Stick to Football, October 2023" (the dated published episode) and documented Keane's spoken disfluency in the ledger.
- Gave Victoria's fridge quote an inline date (**2006 interview**), in-body and in the ledger — was previously "widely published," undated.

**TO REACH A #2 — Originality (single-note thesis):**
- Added a new signature section, **"What David Beckham does when no one is keeping score"**: the Cotswolds beekeeping (27 hives), home-grown veg, harvested honey, nightly cooking — framed as competence/security *for their own sake* (sp Three off the crowd), explicitly set apart from the dread-driven 2am cleaning. Anchored on "I'm never happier than when I'm here" (Country Life / Titchmarsh). It also carries a third honest critic-concession (honey has a label, garden made a magazine) and sets up the "Himself" close.

